STATUS: BLOCKED — template evidence; replace with captured transcript after qemu/Cuttlefish/board run
# ======================================================================
# Template evidence for the Linux-kernel side of the minimum Linux+NPU
# target. This file documents the marker contract that a real captured
# transcript at `docs/evidence/linux/eliza_e1_serial_boot.log` (and its
# sibling kernel-build / DTB-check / OpenSBI-handoff / MMIO-smoke logs)
# must satisfy in order for `make minimum-linux-target-check` to leave
# BLOCKED status and move toward PASS.
#
# This file is NEVER consumed as a real boot transcript:
#   - the file name ends in `.template.log` (not the actual `*.log` paths
#     listed in `docs/evidence/linux/eliza-linux-boot-artifacts.json`), so
#     no gate script reads this file directly.
#   - every documented marker line is prefixed with `# REQUIRED_MARKER:`
#     so that the literal marker string does NOT appear as a bare line in
#     this template, and so that a contributor can `grep` the contract.
#   - the first line of this file is `STATUS: BLOCKED ...`, which the
#     fail-closed gates treat as evidence that real capture has not yet
#     been performed.
#
# claim_boundary: template_evidence_only_no_silicon_or_qemu_boot_claim
# schema_reference: docs/evidence/linux/eliza-linux-boot-artifacts.json
# gate: scripts/check_minimum_linux_target.py
# make_target: minimum-linux-target-check
#
# To replace this template with real evidence:
#   1. Boot Linux on the generated Eliza Rocket AP (Chipyard Verilator) or
#      on the qemu-virt RV64 / Cuttlefish RV64 reference path with the
#      OpenSBI fw_dynamic payload selected by
#      `scripts/locate_chipyard_linux_payload.py --require-preferred`.
#   2. Capture the full UART transcript and the kernel build / DTB /
#      OpenSBI handoff logs using the producers in
#      `docs/evidence/linux/eliza-linux-boot-artifacts.json`.
#   3. Write the resulting transcript to the canonical evidence paths
#      (see `serial_boot_log`, `kernel_build`, `dtb_check`, and
#      `opensbi_handoff` entries in that manifest), NOT to this template.
#   4. Re-run `make minimum-linux-target-check`. The gate moves from
#      BLOCKED to PASS only when every required marker below appears in
#      its captured transcript without the manifest's forbidden strings
#      (`placeholder`, `substitute`, `not run`, `status=FAIL`,
#      `RESULT=FAIL`, `BLOCKED`).
# ======================================================================

# --- serial boot transcript markers ---------------------------------
# These markers must appear verbatim in
# docs/evidence/linux/eliza_e1_serial_boot.log .
# REQUIRED_MARKER: eliza-evidence: target=linux artifact=eliza_e1_serial_boot
# REQUIRED_MARKER: OpenSBI
# REQUIRED_MARKER: Linux version
# REQUIRED_MARKER: Kernel command line:
# REQUIRED_MARKER: eliza-evidence: status=PASS
# REQUIRED_AT_LEAST_ONE_OF: Run /init as init process | Freeing unused kernel memory | Welcome to | login:

# --- kernel build transcript markers --------------------------------
# These markers must appear verbatim in
# docs/evidence/linux/eliza_e1_kernel_build.log .
# REQUIRED_MARKER: eliza-evidence: target=linux artifact=eliza_e1_kernel_build
# REQUIRED_MARKER: CONFIG_ELIZA_E1
# REQUIRED_MARKER: eliza-evidence: status=PASS

# --- DTB check transcript markers -----------------------------------
# These markers must appear verbatim in
# docs/evidence/linux/eliza_e1_dtb_check.log .
# REQUIRED_MARKER: eliza-evidence: target=linux artifact=eliza_e1_dtb_check
# REQUIRED_MARKER: eliza,e1-npu
# REQUIRED_MARKER: eliza-evidence: status=PASS

# --- OpenSBI fw_dynamic handoff markers -----------------------------
# These markers must appear verbatim in
# docs/evidence/linux/opensbi_fw_dynamic_handoff.log .
# REQUIRED_MARKER: eliza-evidence: target=opensbi artifact=opensbi_fw_dynamic_handoff
# REQUIRED_MARKER: OpenSBI
# REQUIRED_MARKER: Next Address
# REQUIRED_MARKER: eliza-evidence: status=PASS

# --- Linux MMIO smoke transcript markers ----------------------------
# These markers must appear verbatim in
# docs/evidence/linux/e1-mmio-smoke.log .
# REQUIRED_MARKER: eliza-evidence: target=linux artifact=e1-mmio-smoke
# REQUIRED_MARKER: E1_NPU_BASE=0x10020000
# REQUIRED_MARKER: eliza-evidence: status=PASS

# --- Generated-AP Linux smoke markers (Chipyard verilator) ----------
# These markers must appear verbatim in
# build/chipyard/eliza_rocket/verilator-linux-smoke.log . The same
# `OpenSBI` and `Linux version` strings are also re-validated by
# `scripts/check_minimum_linux_npu_target.py` against this boot log.
# REQUIRED_MARKER: OpenSBI
# REQUIRED_MARKER: Linux version
# REQUIRED_MARKER: eliza-evidence: status=PASS

# --- Forbidden strings ---------------------------------------------
# These strings must NEVER appear in a real captured transcript at the
# canonical evidence paths above. They appear here only as anti-patterns
# so a contributor can grep for them after capture. The fail-closed gate
# treats their presence as immediate FAIL.
# FORBIDDEN: placeholder
# FORBIDDEN: substitute
# FORBIDDEN: not run
# FORBIDDEN: status=FAIL
# FORBIDDEN: RESULT=FAIL
# FORBIDDEN: BLOCKED

# End of template. Real captured transcripts replace the canonical
# `.log` files above; this template file stays in place as the
# documented marker contract.
